Anthropic’s products are easiest to understand in 4 buckets:

1. Claude app
This is Anthropic’s main AI assistant for everyday use on web, desktop, and mobile. You use it for writing, summarizing, research, brainstorming, coding help, and file analysis. Example: a student uploads lecture notes and asks Claude to turn them into a study guide; a PM pastes a product brief and asks for launch messaging. Anthropic offers Claude in Free, Pro, Max, Team, and Enterprise plans, with higher tiers giving more usage and business features.

2. Claude API / developer platform
This is the product for developers who want to build Claude into their own apps, workflows, or agents. Anthropic’s docs describe the Claude API as a REST API, with the Messages API as the main interface. Example: a startup builds a customer support assistant into its website, or an internal tool that reads PDFs and drafts account summaries. Anthropic’s developer console has also been consolidated under platform.claude.com.

3. Claude Code
This is Anthropic’s coding-focused agent for developers. It runs in the terminal, understands a codebase, can edit files, run commands, and help ship software faster. Example: you open a repo, run claude, and ask it to trace a bug, update a React component, write tests, and explain the changes. Pro and Max plans can include Claude Code access, and Anthropic positions it as a bridge between ideation and implementation.

4. Claude Agent SDK
This is for teams that want to build their own production agents using the same loop and tools behind Claude Code. Anthropic says it supports things like reading files, running commands, web search, and code edits, programmatically from Python and TypeScript. Example: an engineering team builds an internal release agent that inspects logs, opens files, proposes patches, and drafts incident notes automatically.

A few related things people often confuse with “products”:

Claude models
These are the AI models themselves, not separate end-user products. They power the app, API, and coding tools. Example: when you call Anthropic from your app, you choose a Claude model for speed, cost, or quality depending on the task.

Connectors
These extend Claude by letting it connect to other tools and data sources. Anthropic says custom connectors via remote MCP are available across Claude, Cowork, and Claude Desktop on several plans. Example: connect Claude to internal docs so it can answer questions grounded in company knowledge.
